    "causal_summary": "Smart-routing umbrella skill for application code work. Detects the project stack from marker files (Webflow, React/Next.js, Go) then classifies intent and loads stack-aware resources. Three live stacks: WEBFLOW (Webflow / vanilla animation web with motion.dev / GSAP / Lenis / HLS / Swiper / FilePond signals), REACT (kerkmeester-style Next.js 14 App Router + vanilla-extract + motion v12 + react-hook-form/zod + react-aria + Untitled UI + next-themes), GO (gin + sqlc + pgx + Postgres + go-playground/validator + golang-jwt). Cross-stack pairing doc captures the React↔Go API contract, JWT handoff, error envelope shape, CORS, and deploy topology. Other stacks (Node.js without React/Next, React Native, Swift) fall through to UNKNOWN — this skill does not own them.",
